// Raspberry Pi deployment contract
// Files: docs/RASPBERRY_PI_DEPLOYMENT.md, scripts/deploy.sh, scripts/systemd/worktracker.service

// scripts/deploy.sh
// - resolves repo root relative to the script location
// - requires .env and the target compose file (default docker-compose.prod.yml)
// - supports either `docker compose` or legacy `docker-compose`
// - refuses to run with uncommitted git changes
// - performs `git pull --ff-only`
// - runs `<compose> -f docker-compose.prod.yml build --pull`, then `up -d`, then `ps`

// scripts/systemd/worktracker.service
// - Type=oneshot with RemainAfterExit=yes
// - expects clone path /opt/worktracker/worktracker by default
// - defaults User/Group to pi
// - ExecStart and ExecReload both call scripts/deploy.sh with COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.prod.yml
// - ordered after docker.service and network-online.target

// docs/RASPBERRY_PI_DEPLOYMENT.md
// - deploy target is Raspberry Pi OS Lite 64-bit
// - Docker install path uses get.docker.com with a note about the official repo alternative
// - firewall opens 22/tcp, 80/tcp, 443/tcp
// - production runtime remains HTTP-first by default on WORKTRACKER_HTTP_PORT -> container :80
// - optional HTTPS section points to docs/SSL_SETUP.md and requires adding 443 plus cert/acme mounts
// - backup guidance covers .env, certs/, and deployment overrides
